Date:  28/10/2005
Source:  Dominion Post
Author:
Vol / Page:  B4
Edition:
Quote:  According to the afficionados of New Zealand's musical history, Blerta stands for Bruno Lawrence's Electric Revelation and Travelling Apparition.  For most New Zealanders over 50, however, Blerta is best remembered as a colourful troupe of artists, anarchists and musicians who travelled the highways and byways of New Zealand in a vivdly decorated omnibus of indeterminate age and intermittent reliability. ... Religious allusions aside, Blerta's over-riding message was fun.
